#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.128"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.128:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.128:0.2"
msgid "13. Kusināravagga"
msgstr "13. Kusināra"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.128:0.3"
msgid "128. Kaṭuviyasutta"
msgstr "128. Bitter"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.280"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.128:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā bārāṇasiyaṃ viharati isipatane migadāye."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Benares, in the deer park at "
"Isipatana."

msgctxt "an3.128:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya bārāṇasiṃ "
"piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, "
"entered Benares for alms."

#. VAR: goyogapilakkhasmiṃ → goyogamilakkhasmiṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
#. VAR: caramāno → caramānaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an3.128:1.3"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho bhagavā goyogapilakkhasmiṃ piṇḍāya caramāno aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ "
"rittassādaṃ bāhirassādaṃ muṭṭhassatiṃ asampajānaṃ asamāhitaṃ vibbhantacittaṃ "
"pākatindriyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"While the Buddha was walking for alms near the cow-hitching place at the "
"wavy leaf fig, he saw a disgruntled monk who was looking for pleasure in "
"external things, unmindful, without situational awareness or immersion, with "
"straying mind and undisciplined faculties."

msgctxt "an3.128:1.4"
msgid "Disvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu → bhikkhu bhikkhu mā kho tvaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.128:2.1"
msgid "“Mā kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu, attānaṃ kaṭuviyamakāsi."
msgstr "“Monk, don’t be bitter."

#. VAR: āmagandhena → āmagandhe (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: nānvāssavissantīti → nānvassavissanti (pts1) | nānubandhissanti (mr)
msgctxt "an3.128:2.2"
msgid ""
"Taṃ vata, bhikkhu, kaṭuviyakataṃ attānaṃ āmagandhena avassutaṃ makkhikā "
"nānupatissanti nānvāssavissantīti, netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"If you’re bitter, corrupted by the stench of rotting flesh, flies will, "
"without a doubt, plague and infest you.”"

msgctxt "an3.128:2.3"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu bhagavatā iminā ovādena ovadito saṃvegamāpādi."
msgstr ""
"Hearing this advice of the Buddha, that monk was filled with a sense of "
"urgency."

msgctxt "an3.128:2.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā bārāṇasiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ "
"piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, after the meal, on his return from alms-round, the Buddha told the "
"mendicants what had happened. …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.128:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya bārāṇasiṃ "
"piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an3.128:3.2"
msgid ""
"Addasaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, goyogapilakkhasmiṃ piṇḍāya caramāno aññataraṃ "
"bhikkhuṃ rittassādaṃ bāhirassādaṃ muṭṭhassatiṃ asampajānaṃ asamāhitaṃ "
"vibbhantacittaṃ pākatindriyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an3.128:3.3"
msgid "Disvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.128:4.1"
msgid "‘Mā kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu, attānaṃ kaṭuviyamakāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an3.128:4.2"
msgid ""
"Taṃ vata bhikkhu kaṭuviyakataṃ attānaṃ āmagandhena avassutaṃ makkhikā "
"nānupatissanti nānvāssavissantīti, netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an3.128:4.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, so bhikkhu mayā iminā ovādena ovadito saṃvegamāpādī”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an3.128:4.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññataro bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, one of the mendicants asked the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an3.128:4.5"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho, bhante, kaṭuviyaṃ?"
msgstr "“Sir, what is this ‘bitterness’?"

msgctxt "an3.128:4.6"
msgid "Ko āmagandho?"
msgstr "What is the ‘stench of rotting flesh’?"

msgctxt "an3.128:4.7"
msgid "Kā makkhikā”ti?"
msgstr "And what are the ‘flies’?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.128:5.1"
msgid "“Abhijjhā kho, bhikkhu, kaṭuviyaṃ;"
msgstr "“Desire is bitterness;"

msgctxt "an3.128:5.2"
msgid "byāpādo āmagandho;"
msgstr "ill will is the stench of rotting flesh;"

msgctxt "an3.128:5.3"
msgid "pāpakā akusalā vitakkā makkhikā."
msgstr "and bad, unskillful thoughts are the flies."

msgctxt "an3.128:5.4"
msgid ""
"Taṃ vata, bhikkhu, kaṭuviyakataṃ attānaṃ āmagandhena avassutaṃ makkhikā "
"nānupatissanti nānvāssavissantīti, netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatīti."
msgstr ""
"If you’re bitter, corrupted by the stench of rotting flesh, flies will, "
"without a doubt, plague and infest you.”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.281"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an3.128:6.1"
msgid "Aguttaṃ cakkhusotasmiṃ,"
msgstr "“When your eyes and ears are unguarded,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:6.2"
msgid "indriyesu asaṃvutaṃ;"
msgstr "and you’re not restrained in your sense faculties,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:6.3"
msgid "Makkhikānupatissanti,"
msgstr "flies—those lustful thoughts—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:6.4"
msgid "saṅkappā rāganissitā."
msgstr "will plague you."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an3.128:7.1"
msgid "Kaṭuviyakato bhikkhu,"
msgstr "A mendicant who’s bitter,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:7.2"
msgid "āmagandhe avassuto;"
msgstr "corrupted by the stench of rotting flesh,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:7.3"
msgid "Ārakā hoti nibbānā,"
msgstr "is far from being extinguished,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:7.4"
msgid "vighātasseva bhāgavā."
msgstr "frustration is their lot."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an3.128:8.1"
msgid "Gāme vā yadi vāraññe,"
msgstr "Whether in village or wilderness,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: samathamattano → samamattano (bj, s1-3, km) | sammamattano (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.128:8.2"
msgid "aladdhā samathamattano;"
msgstr "if they don’t find serenity in themselves,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Pareti → care (s1-3) | careti (mr)
msgctxt "an3.128:8.3"
msgid "Pareti bālo dummedho,"
msgstr "the fool, void of wisdom,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:8.4"
msgid "makkhikāhi purakkhato."
msgstr "is honored only by flies."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an3.128:9.1"
msgid "Ye ca sīlena sampannā,"
msgstr "But those who have ethics,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:9.2"
msgid "paññāyūpasameratā;"
msgstr "lovers of wisdom and peace,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:9.3"
msgid "Upasantā sukhaṃ senti,"
msgstr "they, being peaceful, sleep well,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:9.4"
msgid "nāsayitvāna makkhikā”ti."
msgstr "since they’ve got rid of the flies.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.128:9.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
